- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The problem of finding an optimal sequence to repair the infrastructure components can be formulated as an optimization problem, which is a common topic in AI. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Although not directly related to cryptography or security, the paper deals with the resilience of physical infrastructure after disasters, which can be seen as a security concern. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The problem of finding an optimal sequence to repair the infrastructure components can also be seen as a scheduling problem, which is a common topic in data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper deals with the problem of maintaining the health of physical infrastructure components, which can be seen as a software engineering problem in the context of maintenance and reliability.
